1061
00:54:41,778 --> 00:54:46,147
I think he would
simply refuse to--

1062
00:54:46,182 --> 00:54:49,419
to be part of it.

1063
00:54:50,587 --> 00:54:53,454
Moore: Jesus would refuse
to be part of it,

1064
00:54:53,490 --> 00:54:55,458
but he probably had
a special place up there

1065
00:54:55,492 --> 00:54:58,427
for whoever leaked
a secret Citibank memo

1066
00:54:58,461 --> 00:55:01,828
about their plan to rule the world.

1067
00:55:01,865 --> 00:55:03,856
Back in 2005 and 2006,

1068
00:55:03,900 --> 00:55:06,232
Citigroup wrote
three confidential memos

1069
00:55:06,269 --> 00:55:10,729
to their wealthiest investors
about how things were going.

1070
00:55:10,774 --> 00:55:13,174
They reached the conclusion
that the United States

1071
00:55:13,209 --> 00:55:15,439
was no longer
really a democracy,

1072
00:55:15,478 --> 00:55:18,242
but had become a plutonomy--

1073
00:55:18,281 --> 00:55:21,375
a society controlled exclusively
by and for the benefit

1074
00:55:21,418 --> 00:55:24,512
of the top 1%
of the population

1075
00:55:24,554 --> 00:55:26,647
who now had
more financial wealth

1076
00:55:26,690 --> 00:55:30,319
than the bottom 95% combined.

1077
00:55:30,360 --> 00:55:33,591
The memo gloated about the growing gap
between rich and poor

1078
00:55:33,630 --> 00:55:37,088
and how they were now
the new aristocracy

1079
00:55:37,133 --> 00:55:41,069
and that there was no end in sight
for the gravy train they were on.

1080
00:55:41,104 --> 00:55:44,665
There was, though,
one problem.

1081
00:55:44,708 --> 00:55:46,232
According toCitigroup,

1082
00:55:46,276 --> 00:55:48,870
the most potent
and short-term threat

1083
00:55:48,912 --> 00:55:50,709
would be societies demanding

1084
00:55:50,747 --> 00:55:53,341
a more equitable share
of the wealth.

1085
00:55:53,383 --> 00:55:57,752
In other words,
the peasants might revolt.

1086
00:55:57,787 --> 00:56:00,153
Citigroup lamented
that the non-rich

1087
00:56:00,190 --> 00:56:02,658
might not have
much economic power,

1088
00:56:02,692 --> 00:56:06,219
but they do have
equal voting power with the rich.

1089
00:56:06,262 --> 00:56:09,231
One person, one vote.

1090
00:56:09,265 --> 00:56:11,927
And that's what
really scares them--

1091
00:56:11,968 --> 00:56:14,402
that we can still vote.

1092
00:56:14,437 --> 00:56:17,736
In fact, we have
99% of the votes

1093
00:56:17,774 --> 00:56:20,572
and they only have 1%.

1094
00:56:23,646 --> 00:56:27,605
So why do the 99%
put up with this?

1095
00:56:27,650 --> 00:56:31,086
According to Citigroup,
